        <abstract>
            <p>Discussion of Mrs Agassiz’s letter [to Mary Lyell, forwarded to CD] regarding S. American glacial action,</p>
            <p>with comments on Bunbury’s letter on temperate plants.</p>
            <p>Refers to opinions of Agassiz, David Forbes, Hooker, and CD on glacial period and glaciers.</p> 
<p>Wishes he had published a long chapter on glacial period [<hi rend="italic">Natural selection</hi>, pp. 535–66] written ten years ago.</p> 
            <p>Tells of death of his sister, Catherine, and other family matters.</p>
        </abstract>
